nitial duties and complementary pairing internally. 10) Store persistent state for runtime updates: the PWM handle, the channels array, the current dutyCycles[3] (in percent), and the per-channel deadTimes[] and phases[]. 11) Configure the diagnostic LED GPIO (the pin designated for ISR toggling) as push-pull output using the IfxPort API after PWM initialization. Outputs start in a safe state and then operate with the configured initial duty, dead-time, and min-pulse constraints.",
